            {# How to use #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üß© How to use</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        Add <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-js="collapse"</code> to the toggle button and set
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-target</code> to the navbar body ID.
                        The script opens or closes the navbar body, toggles the
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.show</code> class, and updates
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-expanded</code> automatically.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Sizes (Breakpoints) #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìè Breakpoints</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                    These classes control the breakpoint at which the navbar switches
                    between desktop layout and collapsed layout.
                    Each one sets its own responsive behavior. <br>
                    The default <code class="text-bold text-primary">.navbar</code> uses the <code class="text-bold text-primary">md</code> breakpoint.
                    </p>
                    <p class="p-1">
                        The current configuration sets the typographic baseline to <code class="text-bold text-primary">1rem = 10px</code>, using
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">html { font-size: 62.5%; }</code>.
                    </p>

                    <div class="row mt-2">
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.navbar</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">Collapses at 76.8rem (768px)</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.navbar-xs</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">Collapses at 42.5rem (425px)</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
