                </div>

                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        Alignment is controlled via classes on
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.navbar-body</code>.
                        On desktop, you can align the content to the left, center, or right.
                    </p>

                    <div class="row my-2">
                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.left</code><br>
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.start</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">Aligns the navbar content to the left.</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2 h-100">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.center</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">Centers the navbar content.</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.right</code><br>
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.end</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">Aligns the navbar content to the right.</p>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="p-1">
                        When the navbar is collapsed
                        (<code class="text-bold text-primary">.navbar-body.show</code> on smaller screens),
                        you can use the <code class="text-bold text-primary">bp-*</code> variants to change
                        the alignment only in collapsed mode.
                    </p>

                    <div class="row my-2">

                        <div class="col-12 col-4-xs">
                            <article class="card p-2">
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.bp-left</code><br>
                                <code class="text-bold text-primary">.bp-start</code>
                                <p class="text-sm mt-1">
                                    Aligns items to the left <b>when collapsed</b>.
                                </p>
                            </article>
                        </div>

